# etl-app

Tool to consume json incidents and output them in a specified sort order in CSV format

## Como compilar

To build the app just run `make build` then the binary will be in `build/`

## Tests & coverage

To run get tests just run `make test` or to get tests with coverage run `make coverage`

## Expected variables

| Variables       |  Command && Shortcut            |                Description                |
| --------------- | :--------------------:          | :---------------------------------------: |
| sortdirection            | -sortdirection        | sort incidents by direction command line argument value must be one of "ascending, descending" |

## Run the app

To run the app make `./build/etl-app` if you want to send commands then make `./build/etl-app -variablename=value` the `-` is mandatory
If you wan to send more than 1 variable must be separete with whitespace then `-` for example `./build/etl-app -sortdirection=ascending`
